ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I strongly recommend students in relevant area to select it. But it is also really time-consuming. You should consider the time you can devote.

It is a fantastic course to code numerical methods. The professor is incredibly talented and caring, however, the problem sets do take a considerable amount of time to debug and may have tedious hand calculations. It is worth the effort if your research in involving systems of equations of numerical approximations.

It is a course that teaches computer based numerical approximations. I would recommend it to another student because the information taught in the class is useful in a number of different fields of study.
A lot of work but one gets a lot out of it. Support by professor and TAs is incredible so is feedback on problem sets.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It helps me to have a better understand of numerical solution of different functions.
This course helped me in numerical modeling of problems in my research. It is also a great class to refresh linear algebra terms and definitions.
This course taught me useful computer and computational skills. It contributed greatly to my research work.
